block docs
  h1 Links

  p By adding the #[code .u-stretched-link] class to a link, it make the "block"
    |  clickable via a pseudo-element.
    br
    | To acheive it, the pseudo-element is #[em stretched] to recover the nearest
    |  parent with #[code position: relative] property.

  p For the next example, the Card component already have a position set by default,
    |  but if it's not the case, you can add the #[code .u-pos-r] utility class.

  .p-example
    .o-row
      .o-col.u-12(class="u-3@md")
        .c-card
          .c-card__img
            img(src="../assets/data/lake-1.jpg", alt="Photo by Adam Vradenburg on Unsplash")
          .c-card__header
            .c-card__title.u-h5.u-mb-0 Card title
          .c-card__body
            span Add some text inside the card.
              br
              | ok more text here.
          .c-card__footer
            a(href="#").c-button.c-button--primary.u-stretched-link Action
  pre.code(data-lang="HTML").u-mb-2
    code
      :highlight(lang="html")
        <div class="c-card"><!-- the .u-pos-r is not required with the card component -->
          <div class="c-card__img">
            <img src="../assets/data/lake-1.jpg" alt="Photo by Adam Vradenburg on Unsplash">
          </div>
          <div class="c-card__header">
            <div class="c-card__title u-h5 u-mb-0">Card title</div>
          </div>
          <div class="c-card__body">
            <span>Add some text inside the card.<br>ok more text here.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="c-card__footer">
            <a class="c-button c-button--primary u-stretched-link" href="#">Link</a>
          </div>
        </div>
